CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1970, pg. 1, reads: "Pittsburgh Panther Posters - Highly visible evidence that the Black Panther Party and all of its workings have entered the Pittsburgh scene can be witnesses in Homewood not only by the opening of two meals-for-shool youngster projects, a Homewood-Brushton office for a Panther wing, and an organizing drive, but also by these large full-newspaper-size wall posters of the Black Community News Service plastered abundantly on store windows in Homewood-Brushton area, plus distribution of campaign buttons reading 'Free Huey' and other Panther slogans."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Daw's shop with boarded up door and Black Panther Manifesto on Bobby Seal, Homewood
